Package com.example.freeturilo.core

Enum SystemState

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<SystemState>
      • com.example.freeturilo.core.SystemState
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<SystemState>
    public enum SystemState
extends java.lang.Enum<SystemState>
    State of the Freeturilo system.

    Values of this enum represent different states of the Freeturilo system. There are static methods declared within the enum that help use it.

    Version:
    1.0.0
    Author:
    Miko≈Çaj Terzyk
    See Also:
    STARTED, DEMO, STOPPED, getButtonId(com.example.freeturilo.core.SystemState), getState(int)

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant Description
      DEMO
      Represents the state in which the Freeturilo System uses static NextBike data instead of dynamically updating it.
      STARTED
      Represents the normal working system state.
      STOPPED
      Represents the state in which the Freeturilo API refuses to properly respond to requests sent by unauthorized (non-admin) users.
